as the year ends …..

I want to remind you that life gives you what you need. 

lessons and triumphs. 

hard times. 

the best of times. 

and the most mundane of days. 

so go with the flow. 

go with life. 

look for the opportunity and the beauty in the small things. 

take your time. 

go slow. 

and enjoy the moment. 

learn from the challenges. 

look back with heartfelt gratitude. 

and go forward with excitement and anticipation. 

good things are coming. 

many challenges are behind you. 

but most importantly. 

fall in love with this moment. 

an ending and a new beginning.

a moment in between. 

🤍

I’ve been pushed way out of my comfort zone this year when it comes to my emotional stability and security. 

my family life has been triggered …. A LOT. 

my place of living has been through MANY reality checks …. 

meaning a lot of people have “relocated over this past year” or have done some significant renovations and innovations within our relationship as well. 

I’ve been searching for a place as to where I belong for a while now. 

but for me, that place I’ve been searching for is strictly internal. 

my inner peace and my inner center have gone through some pretty important challenges in 2022.

I intend to keep that momentum consistent. 

I’ve suffered with my insecurities and my twisted self-worth beliefs all the while making continuous breakthroughs by LEARNING to honor myself and my priorities. 

I am grateful to have continuously transformed in a way so that I can recognize true value in others and most importantly within myself. 

thank you …..

every single one of you …..

who have inspired me to dig deep within my ego this year, and caused me to realize where I needed to own my own shit and take that shit and clean it up. 

I’ve said it before and I’ll say it again •

the transformations are not a one size fits all kinda lifestyle • 

AND the weight that we need to lose in order to make that ish happen isn’t on our physical bodies. 

transforming my mind trickled down into my heart which opened up my soul to new beginnings. 

2023 •

you look pretty ….

in all the ways. 

🤍

this year, I have learned that grief and gratitude can co-exist. 

that I can feel my heart crack down the middle, and be thankful for that pain because it meant that I have lived fully and loved deeply. 

that I didn’t hide from life, but instead I chose to pour my whole self into the act of beautiful, hard, and messy living. 

I learned that I can love the life that I have now while still taking time to grieve the paths that I didn’t walk - 

the lIves that I didn’t get to live - 

the people who are no longer traveling this path beside me - 

and the visions of a future I once had that can no longer be. 

I learned that so many times in life, we don’t know that the last time that we do something is going to be the last. 

that it often sneaks up on us unexpectedly.

and while we can’t prevent the lasts, we can love what we have now while it’s still here just a little bit more. 

this year, I have learned that my heart can handle so much more than I ever gave it credit for …..

that it’s soft but mighty. 

that it’s far stronger than I ever realized. 

stronger than I even know now. 

and while I sometimes wish it didn’t have to be so strong - 

I’m grateful for this beating heart for always reminding me that I’m still here. 

still breathing. 

I’m grateful for its gentle wisdom and soft nudges. 

and most of all - 

I’m grateful that in the joy and in the pain •

the hope and the heartache •

it still knows love. 

if December feels a little bit heavier for you this year …..

know that you are not alone. 

it may be hard to feel gratitude for the heavy moments right now - 

but I am learning that enormous grief is the result of enormous love. 

and the fact that you’ve gotten to love something so deeply -

whether it’s a person •

a dream •

an experience •

or just life itself …….

that is worth everything. 

be good to you -

most times when we think all is going wrong - 

it’s actually all going right. 

🤍

xx A

you are on a journey with no defined beginning - middle or end. 

there are no wrong turns - 

there is just being. 

and your job is to be as you as you can be. 

it’s not about becoming anything. 

it’s about unbecoming everything that isn’t really you so that you can become who you were meant to be in the first place. 

you have to choose yourself. 

even when others refuse to. 

self love is choosing yourself and choosing yourself is self care. 

you’re entertaining the wrong things with the wrong people because you’re struggling with loving yourself.

it’s okay to take a break - 

a moment for yourself. 

it’s okay to be selfish if it means rediscovering your own power and your own happiness. 

so moving forward. 

be kind to yourself. 

there is never a better time to be kind. 

to remind yourself of how far you’ve come - not bringing up how far you still need to go. 

to care for yourself in a way that only you can - without relying on the words & actions of others. 

to fall in love with taking care of yourself - without feeling obligated or guilty for it. 

it’s time to create an unbreakable love for yourself - that cannot be broken by the unkind words and actions of others. 

your mind is a powerful thing. 

when you fill it with positive thoughts - 

YOUR LIFE WILL START TO CHANGE! 

practice kindness. 

be thankful. 

breathe deeply. 

enjoy life. 

and most importantly - 

LOVE. 

🤍

so often, we say we wish we would have known back then what we know now. 

we dream of returning to our pasts so that we can make new choices. 

so that we can live more ….. “fully.”

so that we can cherish what we had while we had it and love it all just a little bit more. 

…. but we can’t go back. 

and if we’re always dreaming of going back ….

we are going to miss out on what we have right now. 

and one day …. 

today is the day that we will be wishing to return to. 

today is the day that we will wish that we had loved just a little bit more. 

so this is what we can do. 

we can give this present moment our undivided attention. 

we can tell the people that we love exactly how we feel while they’re here. 

we can take the risks that we are so afraid to take and choose bravery over backing down. 

and every once in awhile …..

we can step out of our thinking minds and into our feeling hearts. 

we can be here. 

exactly where we are. 

without always searching for something to change or fix. 

and we can give this whole living thing our very best shot. 

maybe we can’t go back and change the past. 

but we can create a present moment so beautiful that it doesn’t need to be changed. 

life isn’t perfect. 

it isn’t meant to be. 

but we should always love the beautiful messiness & the perfect imperfections of this life that we are living right now. 

we can be here. 

now. 

present. 

open-hearted. 

ready to live the fullness of our lives. 

I still have some unfinished business to deal with from 2022. 

for the first time ever in my life - I’m not ready - not prepared to start “new”. 

in 2022 I learned that the universe truly does have my back. 

in 2023, I will stand firm and have my own. 

this year I grew my wings. 

next year. 

I dare to fly. 

thanks for riding with me - 

now let’s buckle up ……..

to where we’re meant to land. 

even if the destination is still unknown to us in this moment. 

remember. 

you can’t wait until life isn’t hard anymore before you decide to be happy. 

Happy New Year My People. 

🤍

xx The G Unit

the last few weeks I’ve been sleeping by 8pm. 

I know - it sounds CRAZY 🤪

but my body has been thriving from the rest and my HRV levels are reflecting it. 

I have become such a morning person over the last few years. 

I may wake up GROGGY 🤨 and need a double scoop of energize every now and again • 

but I have found such peace and solitude in my morning routine. 

waking up to the stillness in my home - which I have spent the last 2 years refocusing all of the bad energy into GOOD ……. 

there is no better feeling to me. 

I feel safe. 

something I took for granted. 

I wake up feeling grateful for the abundance of what life has given me. 

never did I ever think that I would be this happy being where I am today. 

to think of how scared and angry I was all of those years ago ….. 

when life was happening AND unfolding FOR me. 

the higher power was teaching me •

PATIENCE.

and what I have learned is that patience is not passive. 

on the contrary. 

it is concentrated strength. 

we often want what we want so fucking badly that we ruin it before it begins. 

overthinking. 

fantasizing. 

imagining. 

expecting.

worrying. 

doubting. 

just sit with it. 

just be. 

and let life naturally evolve. 

you see - patience is teaching ME that it’s more than simply learning to wait. 

it’s having learned what is worth MY time. 

be amazing today babe. 

you deserve it!

so you can hear what is being said without the filter of your wounds. 

my pain-body became the filter through which I started to view my life situations.

I was never able to see the link between my emotional pain and my thoughts, being completely identified with both. 

I could not yet see that I was feeding my pain-body with my thoughts.

I was living with the burden of a deeply unhappy self. 

we need to understand that our unhappiness about being unhappy is just another layer of unhappiness. 

don’t do anything. 

do less. 

BUT. 

find out whether it is possible for you to allow those feelings to be there. 

there is space around your unhappiness. 

the space of course comes from when there is inner acceptance of whatever you are experiencing in that present moment. 

on one hand,
we all want to be happy. 

on the other hand,

why?

simple. 

we are always “too busy”.

people always assume that I’m sad because I spend so much time alone. 

people may think, oh I feel sorry for her.

maybe you assume that I do not have any friends. 

the last few years have forced me to become more aware of what is really worth my energy. 

we bitch and we complain about how much our lives suck, but yet we do nothing to change the suck. 

it gets to a point where we sit and live in disgust of what our life has become, but yet we fail to realize that it is only OURSELVES that can make the choice to do something about it. 

so I got serious about what I wanted.

and I made sacrifice after sacrifice. 

I stopped going out every weekend to save money. 

I stopped drinking to black out all of my sadness. 

I started eating better to make myself feel better. 

I started getting up earlier because I want to value my time. 

and I stopped doing things that benefited others but DID NOT benefit myself.

social_posts.post_text:
time decides who you meet in life.

your heart decides who you want in your life. 

and your behavior decides who stays in your life. 

@drlaurenfitz and I met forever and a day ago. 

three years ago when I was presented with some major health issues - I reached out to her • she was weeks into opening @larimarmedllc.

I was scared beyond belief and unsure where my life was headed. 

three years later I can say with great pride that functional medicine along with @larimarmedllc has completely changed my life. 

change is so scary. 

the uncertainty and they emotions that are presented with said change can 100% put you in some major feels. 

but being a patient at @larimarmedllc has been the best decision I have ever made - for myself AND my family. 

it has been beyond a blessing to call Lauren my doctor and a distinct honor to call her my friend. 

one of the MANY reasons that I ride so hard for her is the simple fact that she presents you with two choices - 

evolve or repeat. 

I’ve learned the hard way that we repeat what we do not repair. 

her courage and lead by example lifestyle has inspired me that I can’t change what I refuse to confront. 

life has not been easy for either one of us the last three years …..

but not showing support through it all was never a thought in my mind. 

Lauren has taught me that time is not refundable and that I should always use it with the deepest of intentions. 

stop being scared of your own potential. 

because ultimately we are our choices. 

it takes courage to bloom!

congratulations my dear friend on three years of continuing to GROW a successful medical practice. 

💙

this year I learned that grief and gratitude can co-exist. 

that I can feel my heart crack down the middle and be thankful for the pain because it means that I lived fully and loved deeply - that I didn’t hide from life but instead - chose to pour myself into the whole act of beautiful, hard and messy living. 

I learned that I can love the life that I have now while still taking the time to grief the paths that I didn’t walk. 

the lives that I didn’t get to live. 

the people who are no longer traveling the path beside me. 

the visions of a future that I once had that can no longer be. 

I learned that so many times in life, we don’t know the last time that we do something is going to be the last. 

that it often sneaks up on us unexpectedly.

and that while we can’t predict the lasts, we can love what we have now while it’s still here just a little bit more. 

this year, I leaned that my heart can handle so much more than I ever gave it credit for. 

that it’s soft but mighty. 

that it’s far stronger than I ever realized - stronger than I even know now. 

and while I sometimes wish it didn’t have to be so strong - 

I’m grateful for this beating heart for reminding me that I’m still here. 

still breathing. 

I’m grateful for its gentle wisdom and soft nudges. 

and most of all - 

I’m grateful that in all the joy and pain - the hope and the heartbreak …… 

it knows love 🤍

forty nine - 

I’m so down.

#TheDayIWasBorn

I’m starting to understand that the universe is not in a hurry ……. 

 I am.

It’s why I am anxious stressed, and disappointed. 

I need to trust that what was meant to be mine will be mine. 

I also need to understand that those things that I need to hear sometimes •

Like you’re doing great and this is tough, but you can do it and you are totally absolutely enough -

……. well, I’m allowed to say those things to myself - 

No one can dictate how, what, why, or when we are allowed to feel.

and that’s because living fully is an emotional experience .

you are responsible for how you respond to your feelings- 

but, you owe no one an explanation for feeling it in the first place.

I don’t know what the future is going to look like - 

But I do know that the one I participate in creating will look very different from the one that has happened to me.

Sometimes life is tough. 

Not all the time - just sometimes.

And when we remember, it’s only sometimes - it becomes a little lighter. 

So I’m going to learn how to distinguish the quiet whisper of my intuition from the incessant chatter in my mind -

Because the more I listen, the more I hear.

so I will be more intentional to stop fighting the tides of my emotions-

because ultimately, freedom is found in directing your energy towards those things that you can control and learning to let go of all that you can’t .

it didn’t happen the way you wanted - 
but it happened the way you needed. 

you’ll see.

everything, in time. 

🤍

Beautiful girl, when you are finished falling.
after you hit rock bottom and watch yourself come  apart into a million pieces.

no one is sticking around to to help you collect yourself.

no one is sticking around to pick through your pieces to decide which parts of you are worth keeping.

That’s for you to decide.

So stay down for as long as you need to.

This is the most important.

Take your time.

Pay attention.

You already broke.

So the easy part is over.

Go slow …… 

I know, you thought the breaking was the most painful chapter.

It wasn’t.

Turn the page.

The next part is much longer.

It’s the healing. 

The rise. 

The come back. 

It’s the birth of the new you.

And it ain’t easy.

But you are strong and brave and worth it.

You’ll have to leave a lot of yourself behind.

you have to let go of all the parts of you that you have outgrown.

We’re not making ourselves small anymore.

We’re not bending to fit where we don’t belong anymore.

Do you hear me?

We are going all in.

So count your wounds - every scar ripped open - every drop of blood you bled like a promise - every tear you cried, like a bet in the name of crossing your whole heart - your whole soul - was all for this moment. 

Right here. 

Right now. 

You had to hurt like that to get here to this version of you who knows exactly who she is.

Exactly who she’s not.

and exactly who she will never be AGAIN!

Drop the apologies babe.

We are not sorry anymore for who we are.

we’re not sorry for what we had to do to get here.

and we’re not sorry for the time it took to learn our worth.

Step out of the box of all you were supposed to be according to everyone who wasn’t you, and walk into the you, who is comfortable in her own skin.

It’s time. 

You’ve earned it. 

We no longer wear the expectations of anyone else and we no longer let anyone else decide what we are worth.

Because we know now.

We finally know.

And now it’s time to celebrate it. 

Get up babe.

It doesn’t hurt anymore.

Now go show YOU what you’re made of.

🤍

I’ve been pushed way out of my comfort zone this year when it comes to my emotional stability and security.

my place of living has been through MANY reality checks …. 

meaning a lot of people have “relocated over this past year” or have done some significant renovations and innovations within our relationship as well. 

I’ve been searching for a place as to where I belong for a while now. 

but for me, that place I’ve been searching for is strictly internal. 

my inner peace and my inner center have gone through some pretty important challenges in 2023.

I intend to keep that momentum consistent. 

I’ve suffered with my insecurities and my twisted self-worth beliefs all the while making continuous breakthroughs by LEARNING to honor myself and my priorities. 

I am grateful to have continuously transformed in a way so that I can recognize true value in others and most importantly within myself. 

thank you …..

every single one of you …..

who have inspired me to dig deep within my ego this year, and caused me to realize where I needed to own my own shit and take that shit and clean it up. 

I’ve said it before and I’ll say it again •

the transformations are not a one size fits all kinda lifestyle • 

AND the weight that we need to lose in order to make that ish happen isn’t on our physical bodies. 

transforming my mind trickled down into my heart which opened up my soul to new beginnings. 

2024 •

you look pretty ….

in all the ways.

they don’t know it yet • but when they’re grown and starting their own Christmas traditions - it will be YOU that they mirror. 

your family recipes will grace their Holly dressed table and the classic punch that you spiked will come out after lunch. 

they will search for the same candle scent that you burned to get that nostalgic smell that is woven in it their memories. 

they will play the carols that feel like home …. that feel like you. 

their children’s handmade snowmen and reindeer will be hung with pride just like theirs were • and carrots will be nibbled on Christmas Eve in the same way you did all those years ago. 

morning elves - phantom sleigh bells and Santa photos will create the same joy and excitement for their kids that you created for them. 

for when they think of Christmas - 

they will think of you.

it will be you that they emulate.

you that they remember. 

you that want to be for their kids. 

you’re their memories. 

you’re their magic. 

you’re their Christmas. 

this year I was more intentional to resist the urge to define my successes in metrics, checked boxes and things. 

instead I chose to reflect on growth. 

to acknowledge what I’ve overcome. 

I reminisced on all of the moments that have became memories. 

I made time to give myself credit and to be proud …..

not only of what I have done - 

but of who I am. 

who I have become. 

so, when you reflect on this year and think about what you’re proud of ….

make sure that list also includes you. 

thank you for being here with me this last year.

you have no idea how much your support has meant to me. 

from our family to yours, 

merry everything & happy always.
